.TH QDOS 1 "11 September 2022" "1.0.0" "QDOS man page"

.SH NAME
QDOS \- simulator of generic QuDits OperationS

.SH SYNOPSIS
qdos [options] infile

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B QDOS
is a simulator of controlled physical systems.
It finds its origin in the need to study the properties of different possible physical platforms for the realization of qudits.
Moreover, to be able to fully study such qualities we need to take into account the presence of errors.
.B QDOS
take care also of this simulating arbitrary error sources trough approximations given by the Lindblad Equation.

It takes as input a quantum circuit written in the
.B QDOS
programming language.
Such language has been developed specificaly for the simulator (hence the same name).
Such language have been developed with complete focus to the simplicity of implementations of quantum error correction schemes.

Here we will discuss in details only the options accepted by the program.
For a full description of the program and of the
.B QDOS
language one should refer to the documentations included with the software.
In particular Chapter 1 and 2 of my Master's Thesis.

.SH OPTIONS
.\"TODO::	COMPLETARE LE INFO PER ALCUNE OPZIONI SPECIFICANDO COSA VOGLIONO DIREI TUTTI I POSSIBILI VALORI CHE POSSONO ESSERE DATI AD UNA OPZIONE
.IP --connection_enabled={true|false}
Enable connections among qudit to resolve levels.

.IP --dephasing_enabled={true|false}
Enable the simulation of pure dephasing errors.

.IP --frequency_output={integer}
Sets the number of times the density matrix will be printed when simulating a pulse.

.IP --help
Display this Information.

.IP --in_dir={string}
Set the directory for input files.

.IP --measurement_error={double}
Set the probability of errors in a measurement of a qudit.

.IP --measure_memory={integer}
Set the number of measurement to save.

.IP --n_shots={integer}
Set the number of complete measurements to be performed at the end of the simulation.

.IP --out_dir={string}
Set the directory for the output files.

.IP --out_rho_final={false|bin|dec}
Set the format of the final density matrix to be printed.

.IP --out_rho_simulation={false|bin|dec}
Set the format of the intermediate density matrix to be printed.

.IP --random_seed={false|true|integer}
Set a custom seed for the RNG of QDOS or auto-generate a random seed for it.

.IP --simulation_enabled={true|false}
Enable the simulation of the circuit provided as input.

.IP --simulation_progres={0|1|2}
Set the level of verbosity of the simulator.

.IP --version
Get the version of the installed software.

The options above have default values shuch that a plain call to QDOS (i.e., qdos circ.q) is equivalent to:

qdos --connection_enabled=true --dephasing_enabled=false --frequency_output=32 --in_dir="./input/" --measurement_error=0.0 --measure_memory=10 --n_shots=0 --out_dir="./output/" --out_rho_final=dec --out_rho_simulation=dec --out_schedule=dec --simulation_enabled=true --simulation_progres=2 circ.q

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

